 {"id":"bd-4bhg","title":"Joined-table inheritance polymorphic base queries (multiple child types)","description":"## Problem

`Select::polymorphic_joined::<Child>()` currently supports exactly one joined-inheritance child type. Real-world SQLModel/SQLAlchemy hierarchies often have multiple joined children and base queries must downcast into the correct concrete type.

## Goals
- Define a compile-time, zero-reflection way to represent a polymorphic hierarchy (likely macro-generated enum).
- Build one query that LEFT JOINs all children and projects prefixed columns without collisions.
- Hydrate into the correct enum variant using `Row::prefix_is_all_null(child_table)` checks.

## Acceptance
- [ ] API for declaring the polymorphic enum and the child set (macro or derive)
- [ ] Query builder that produces JOINs + projections for N children
- [ ] Hydration chooses correct variant (prefers most-derived when multiple non-null possible)
- [ ] Unit tests for SQL generation
- [ ] SQLite integration test with 2+ child tables
